{"id":"hashum","term":"Hashum","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Opulent. (1.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:19\">Ezra 2:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 7:22\">Neh. 7:22</a>. (2.) Stood on Ezra’s left hand while he read the law (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 8:4\">Neh. 8:4</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Ezra 2:19","Nehemiah 7:22","Nehemiah 8:4"]}